omic stimulus measures that saved Canada from sinking into an even deeper recession than it has experienced.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/jobs-recovery-depends-more-government-stimulus-georgetti-says-private-sector-too-weak-\">Jobs recovery depends on more governmentstimulus - Georgetti says private sector is too weak to lead job growth</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; The federal government must invest more money in public services and infrastructure to create good jobs and an economic recovery, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\nGeorgetti was commenting on the release by Statistics Canada of labour force figures for January 2010. The unemployment rate remains at 8.3% and 1.53 million Canadian men and women are out of work. &amp;ldquo;There will be no real economic recovery until those who are unemployed are back working again at full-time, family supporting jobs,&amp;rdquo; he says.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/reality-check-women-s-equality\">\"Reality check\" on women\'s equality</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     Labour, women&amp;rsquo;s groups will tell UN Canada is lagging\nOTTAWA &amp;ndash; Labour and women&amp;rsquo;s groups have issued a report which they say is a &amp;ldquo;reality check&amp;rdquo; describing Canada&amp;rsquo;s lagging performance in achieving women&amp;rsquo;s equality. The report will be used at the Beijing +15 meeting at the United Nations in New York, March 1-12.\nRelated Content\n   Related Human Rights &amp;amp; Equality: \n  \n      \n          Aboriginal Workers    \n       \n          Women    \n       \n          Workers of Colour    \n       \n          Workers with Disabilities    \n       \n          Young Workers    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-best-way-eliminate-federal-deficit-put-15-million-unemployed-canadians\">Georgetti says best way to eliminate federal deficit is to put 1.5 million unemployed Canadians back to work</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     Canada needs added stimulus spending, improved EI, tax on global finance\nOTTAWA &amp;ndash; The federal budget has no plan to create jobs for 1.5 million unemployed Canadians and provides no road map to a prosperous economy, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\n&amp;ldquo;We have lost well over 300,000 full-time jobs since October 2008,&amp;rdquo; Georgetti says. &amp;ldquo;There will be no recovery until there is a jobs recovery, but I don&#039;t see much in the budget to achieve that.&amp;rdquo;\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/jobs-crisis-remains-serious-georgetti-says-government-must-do-more-help-laid-workers\">Jobs\'crisis remains serious - Georgetti says government must do more to help laid-off workers</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     \n	OTTAWA &amp;ndash; Unemployment in Canada is far worse today than it was 16 months ago and the federal government must do more to help laid-off workers, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-federal-pension-consultations-too-restricted\">Georgetti says federal pension consultations too restricted</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     \n	CLC leader says Finance Minister will face backlash\n\n	OTTAWA &amp;ndash; Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress, says he is disappointed that pension reform consultations announced by the federal finance minister will include only three meetings open to the public.\n\n	&amp;ldquo;These are not the broadly-based public consultations that we have been promised on pension reform, and the minister is going to face a backlash from frustrated Canadians,&amp;rdquo; Georgetti says.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Pensions &amp; Retirement    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          Retirement Security for Everyone!    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/canadians-need-good-jobs-georgetti-says-unemployment-among-young-workers-also-problem\">Canadians need good jobs Georgetti says -- Unemployment among young workers also a problem</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     \n	OTTAWA &amp;ndash; The availability of good quality and family-supporting jobs for Canadians remains a problem even as the country begins to emerge from a devastating recession, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \n   Related Human Rights &amp;amp; Equality: \n  \n      \n          Young Workers    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          1238    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/canadian-labour-congress-says-break-conservative-budget-implementation-bill\">Canadian Labour Congress says break-up Conservative budget implementation bill</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;minus; The Canadian Labour Congress (CLC) adds its voice to growing calls for the federal government and the opposition parties to sever parts of Bill C-9 that have nothing to do with implementing the government&amp;rsquo;s budget. Bill C-9 includes provisions that would deregulate Canada Post, potentially harming rural postal services.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Pay Equity    \n     \n   Related Human Rights &amp;amp; Equality: \n  \n      \n          Women    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/jobs-recovery-built-temporary-foundation-economic-recovery-hollow-without-full-time-jo\">Jobs Recovery built on temporary foundation - Economic recovery is hollow without full-time jobs in value added sectors</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; April&amp;rsquo;s job numbers are a surprise and welcome news for an economy wearied by unemployment and a staggering loss of family-supporting jobs. But the news isn&amp;rsquo;t all good, warns Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-praises-municipalities-call-improved-cpp\">Georgetti praises municipalities&#039; call for improved CPP </a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress, has renewed his call for improvements to the Canada Pension Plan following a resolution passed at a convention of the Federation of Canadian Municipalities (FCM).\nThe FCM resolution passed on Saturday, May 29, calls for an expansion of the CPP, a federal system of pension insurance, and for the federal government to hold a national summit on pension issues. This position is virtually identical to that of the labour movement.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Pensions &amp; Retirement    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          Municipalities Matter    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-jobs-recovery-too-slow-clc-president-responds-statistics-canada-job-num\">Georgetti says jobs recovery is too slow - CLC president responds to Statistics Canada job numbers</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; Canada&amp;rsquo;s economy is creating full-time jobs but not quickly enough to get us back to where we were 18 months ago, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\n&amp;ldquo;There were full-time jobs created in May but let&amp;rsquo;s remember that we have 176,000 fewer full time jobs now than we had back in October 2008. Unemployment remains a serious problem.&amp;rdquo;\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/atlantic/news/ken-georgetti-mayor-o-keefe-call-improved-cpp\">Ken Georgetti, Mayor O\'Keefe call for improved CPP</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          Atlantic    \n     ST. JOHN&amp;rsquo;S &amp;ndash; An improved Canada Pension Plan is the best way to guarantee the retirement security of Canadians, according to Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress, and His Worship Dennis O&amp;rsquo;Keefe, the mayor of St. John&amp;rsquo;s, Newfoundland and Labrador. The two leaders made their comments at a joint news conference on Monday, June 7.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Pensions &amp; Retirement    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          Municipalities Matter    \n       \n          Retirement Security for Everyone!    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-support-improved-cpp-growing-among-politicians\">Georgetti says support for improved CPP growing among politicians</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; The campaign waged by the labour movement and citizens&amp;rsquo; groups for improvements to the Canada and Quebec Pension Plans is paying off, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress.\n&amp;ldquo;We have been telling political leaders repeatedly that an improved CPP is far and away the best way to guarantee retirement security for Canadians,&amp;rdquo; Georgetti says. &amp;ldquo;We are pleased that some finance ministers have come to agree with us but we intend to keep their feet to the fire.&amp;rdquo;\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Pensions &amp; Retirement    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          Retirement Security for Everyone!    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/ontario/news/largest-g20-protest-puts-people-and-their-safety-first-organizers-support-injunction-pr\">Largest G20 protest puts people and their safety first - Organizers support injunction to prevent use of sonic cannons during Summit</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          Ontario    \n     TORONTO &amp;ndash; The organizers of the June 26 &amp;ldquo;People First!&amp;rdquo; rally say their reason for organizing what&#039;s likely to be the biggest public protest during the G20 Summit was to give ordinary working people a chance to speak out in a place that&#039;s safe and free from the overblown security presence that&#039;s become so commonplace during meetings of the world&#039;s most powerful heads of state.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Climate Change &amp; Energy    \n       \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Threats to Democracy    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          4774    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/pacific/news/georgetti-welcomes-delegates-ituc-congress\">Georgetti welcomes delegates to ITUC congress</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          Pacific    \n     Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress, welcomed 1500 delegates to the Second World Congress of the International Trade Union Confederation (ITUC) on Monday, June 21 in Vancouver. Georgetti told delegates that the Congress is occurring at a critical time for the international labour movement &amp;ndash; a time of global economic crisis that has seen 34 million lose their jobs since 2008.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          4774    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/pacific/news/fight-protect-public-services-byers-tells-ituc\">Fight to protect public services, Byers tells ITUC</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          Pacific    \n     Barbara Byers, Executive Vice-President of the Canadian Labour Congress, has warned the G20 political leaders who will meet in Toronto that they must not attack and erode public services in their countries.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          Municipalities Matter    \n       \n          4774    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/ontario/news/g20-streets-safer-democracy-police-forced-adopt-safer-procedures-use-lrads\">G20 streets safer for democracy- Police forced to adopt safer procedures for use of LRADs</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          Ontario    \n     TORONTO - Toronto&amp;rsquo;s streets will be safer this weekend, as the result of a court ruling earlier today that forced Toronto police to adopt safer operating procedures for their new LRADs (Long Range Acoustic Devices), also known as sonic cannons.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n       \n          Health and Safety    \n       \n          Security and Surveillance    \n     \n   Related Human Rights &amp;amp; Equality: \n  \n      \n          Aboriginal Workers    \n       \n          Women    \n       \n          Workers of Colour    \n       \n          Workers with Disabilities    \n       \n          Young Workers    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-praises-shirley-carr\">Georgetti praises Shirley Carr</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     Says deceased former CLC President was a pioneer \nOTTAWA &amp;ndash; The President of the Canadian Labour Congress has praised the late Shirley Carr as a pioneer in the labour movement and a fearless campaigner against apartheid in South Africa.\nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/statement-ken-georgetti-president-canadian-labour-congress-vandalism-surrounding-toron\">Statement by Ken Georgetti, President of the Canadian Labour Congress on vandalism surrounding Toronto G20 meeting</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     The Canadian Labour Congress abhors the behaviour of a small group of people who have committed vandalism and destroyed property in activities related to the G20 summit in Toronto.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Security and Surveillance    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          4774    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/labour-s-g20-rally-and-march-drew-thousands\">Labour\'s G20 rally and march drew thousands </a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     Up to 30,000 people took part in a peaceful labour-led rally and march in Toronto on June 26 during the G20 Summit of political leaders. Ken Georgetti, CLC president, told those attending the rally that Canada&amp;rsquo;s government wants to convince other G20 countries to make deep cuts to public services. &amp;ldquo;That can only mean dramatically slashing needed public services during a recession. The G20&amp;rsquo;s priorities should be about cutting unemployment &amp;ndash; not cutting the services that help those without a job,&amp;quot; Georgetti said.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n       \n          Security and Surveillance    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          4548    \n       \n          4774    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-good-news-jobs-undercut-losses-manufacturing-sector-clc-president-comme\">Georgetti says good news on jobs undercut by losses in manufacturing sector - CLC President comments on Statistics Canada job numbers for June</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; There was some good news regarding employment in Canada in June but it was undercut by a continuing loss of jobs in the manufacturing sector, says Ken Georgetti, president of the Canadian Labour Congress. Georgetti was responding to the release by Statistics Canada of its monthly Labour Force Survey.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/now-not-time-pull-plug-unemployed-canadian-workers\">Now is not the time to pull the plug on unemployed Canadian workers - CLC president responds to Statistics Canada job numbers</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; &amp;ldquo;Today&amp;rsquo;s appalling jobs report means that the federal government must rethink its plan to pull the plug on the economic stimulus plan as soon as September,&amp;rdquo; says Canadian Labour Congress President Ken Georgetti.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/help-pakistan\">Help Pakistan</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     In times of great hardship and need, the labour movement shows the meaning of solidarity and mobilizes to bring support to workers, their families and their communities at home and around the world.\nWe have all watched with horror the images of the devastation caused by the floods in Pakistan. Emergency relief to aid the victims is essential.\nThe Canadian Labour Congress, in cooperation with the Canadian Red Cross, is working to provide an easy way for union members to make a donation to help the victims and instantly receive a tax receipt.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Health and Medicare    \n       \n          Humanitarian Support    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-uses-labour-day-push-improved-cpp-georgetti-says-let-s-get-job-done\">CLC uses Labour Day to push for improved CPP: Georgetti says, let\'s get the job done</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          National    \n     OTTAWA &amp;ndash; The president of the Canadian Labour Congress is using Labour Day celebrations to continue the push for improvements to the Canada and Quebec Pension Plans.\nRelated Content\n   Related Issue: \n  \n      \n          Pensions &amp; Retirement    \n     \n   Related Campaign: \n  \n      \n          Retirement Security for Everyone!    \n     \nread more</p><p><strong><a  href=\"http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/labour-day-2010-clc-officers-appearing-across-canada\">Labour Day 2010 - CLC Officers Celebrating Across Canada</a></strong><br />\r\n(<a  href=\"http://course.downes.ca/feed/\"></a>)  \n   Region: \n  \n      \n          Nation